                  <decoDesc>
                    <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d1">
                      Decorative designs: a line of black dots or alternating red and black dots occurs between the hymns (e.g., <locus target="#2r #2v #4r #4v" facs="002 003 004 005">fols. 2r, 2v, 4r, 4v</locus>)
                    </decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                    <list>
                      <item xml:id="a1">
                      <desc type="ScribalNoteCommencing">
                      <locus target="#1r" facs="001">Fol. 1r</locus> Scribal note on commencing the work:
                      <foreign xml:lang="gez">በስመ፡ አብ፡ ወወልድ፡<gap reason="omitted"/> ወጠንኩ፡ ጽሒፈ፡ ዚቅ፡ ዘአስተጋብእዎ፡ ሊቃውንተ፡ ጐንደር፡ ኅሪት፡ ወሠናይት፡ እምብሉይ፡ ወሐዲስ፡ በብዝኃ፡ ጥበብ፡ ረቂቅ፡ ንኅነ፡ ንጽሕፍ፡ በድርሳነ፡ ያሬድ፡</foreign>,
                      “I begin to write Ziq, which was collected with great wisdom by good and chosen scholars of Gondar, based on Old and New Testament. We write according to the work of Yared: . . .
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e1">
                      <desc>
                      <locus target="#111" facs="111">Fol. 111</locus> fore edge has been cut off, leaving only the inner two columns of text
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e2">
                      <desc>
                      <locus target="#112" facs="112">Fol. 112</locus>fore edge has been cut off, leaving only the inner one column
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="a2">
                      <desc type="RecordTransaction">
                      <locus target="#112v" facs="113">Fol. 112v</locus> Record of transaction in Amharic, for lending one bucket of wheat (upper), for payment: on Nahase 26, 1951 (EC) “I received 24 birr.” The writer is Tigriñña
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="a3">
                      <desc>
                      <locus target="#Inside back cover" facs="113">Fols. Inside,, </locus> list of names
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e4">
                      <desc>
                      words of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#7v #8r #18r #27v" facs="008 018 028">folss. 7v, 8r, 18r, 27v, </locus>, etc.);
                      and lines of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#9r #12r #13v #14v" facs="009 012 014 015">9r, 12r, 13v, 14v, </locus>, etc.);
                      and in the upper margin with a symbol (+) marking the location where the text is to be inserted (<locus target="#50r" facs="050"> f. 50r, col. 3, line 16</locus>; <locus target="#59r" facs="059"> f. 59r, col. 3, line 9</locus>);
                      erasure markings are visible (<locus target="#40r" facs="040">40r, </locus>);
                      text has been removed (e.g., <locus target="#24r #40r #63r" facs="024 040 063">24r, 40r, 63r</locus>)
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                    </list>
                  </additions>
                  <bindingDesc>
                    <binding xml:id="binding" contemporary="true">
                        <decoNote xml:id="b1">Parchment, 197 x 163 x 55 mm, four Coptic chain stitches attached with bridle attachments to rough-hewn boards of the traditional wood.</decoNote>
